The paper deals with the problem of sampling and reconstructing signals from a union of linear subspaces in a Hilbert space. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), signal processing (cs.SI), and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper discusses several recent results in these areas and presents a new iterative projection algorithm for signal recovery. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT, cs.LG, and cs.NA, followed by cs.SI and cs.CV.
